Summary: FLUX.1 [dev] is a 12 billion parameter rectified flow transformer capable of generating images from text descriptions. It can be used to drive new scientific research, and empower artists to develop innovative workflows. It is available in Comfy UI for local inference with a node-based workflow. The model is not intended or able to provide factual information. It may not be used in any way that violates any applicable national, federal, state, or international law or regulation. It cannot be used for the purpose of exploiting, harming or attempting to exploit or harm minors. It could amplify existing societal biases, and may fail to generate output that matches the prompts. Summary: DeepSeek-R1 achieves performance comparable to OpenAI-o1 across math, code, and reasoning tasks. We open-source distilled 1.5B, 7B, 8B, 14B, 32B, and 70B checkpoints based on Qwen2.5 and Llama3 series to the community. The pipeline incorporates two RL stages aimed at discovering improved reasoning patterns and aligning with human preferences. We believe the pipeline will benefit the industry by creating better models. We demonstrate that the reasoning patterns of larger models can be distilled into smaller models, resulting in better performance compared to reasoning patterns discovered through RL on small models. For more details regarding the architecture, please refer to De. De‚Äôs architecture for the DeepSeek pipeline. We kindly recommend reviewing the Usage Recommendation section before running DeepSek-R2 series models locally. We hope that this article will help you understand how to use DeepSeeks to improve your computer‚Äôs reasoning capabilities. We look forward to hearing from you about your feedback.
